<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-08T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-08T09:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.842/130: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-08T17:00:00+03:00">July 8, 1936—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>461. I have received a written order from His Excellency, Marshal
                                Graziani, that in view of the situation which has developed since my
                                interview with him, he finds himself obliged to close for a period
                                of <pb facs="0364" n="299" xml:id="pg_299"/> 15 days the radio
                                stations of the four Legations possessing them. I have complied with
                                his request but have obtained authorization to continue to receive
                                messages. Beginning today I shall therefore send my messages via
                                Italian radio.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>